WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.503 --> 00:00:03.605
<i>In medicine today.</i>

2
00:00:03.738 --> 00:00:05.707
<i>technologies like</i>
<i>artificial intelligence</i>
<i>have pretty much taken over.</i>

3
00:00:05.840 --> 00:00:08.543
Is fluconazole contraindicated
with olanzapine and sotalol?

4
00:00:08.676 --> 00:00:10.712
<i>Fluconazole is contraindicated.</i>

5
00:00:10.845 --> 00:00:14.682
Mr. Miller. I realized
fluconazole will interact
with your other meds.

6
00:00:14.816 --> 00:00:16.416
I'll find an alternative.

7
00:00:16.551 --> 00:00:17.852
I don't know how doctors keep
all that stuff in their head.

8
00:00:17.986 --> 00:00:19.954
I know. it's crazy.

9
00:00:20.087 --> 00:00:21.756
<i>Would you like to know more</i>
<i>about fluconazole?</i>

10
00:00:21.890 --> 00:00:23.825
I already handled that. Nurse.

11
00:00:23.958 --> 00:00:26.728
<i>It seemed like AI had answers</i>
<i>for everything around here.</i>

12
00:00:26.861 --> 00:00:28.195
<i>Except maybe those two.</i>

13
00:00:28.730 --> 00:00:31.833
- I really like your clogs.
- Oh. thanks.

14
00:00:31.966 --> 00:00:34.334
Uh. yeah.
they're prescription.

15
00:00:34.702 --> 00:00:36.704
Um. I-I have
unusually flat feet.

16
00:00:36.838 --> 00:00:38.773
which makes. um.
buying shoes difficult.

17
00:00:38.907 --> 00:00:41.408
but it saved
all the men in my family
from going off to war.

18
00:00:41.543 --> 00:00:43.210
Oh.

19
00:00:43.343 --> 00:00:46.313
Sorry. man.
He got away from me.

20
00:00:46.915 --> 00:00:48.016
You're welcome.

21
00:00:48.382 --> 00:00:50.585
She didn't want to
hear about your feet. man.

22
00:00:52.554 --> 00:00:55.088
<i>Maybe AI would never</i>
<i>figure out human love.</i>

23
00:00:56.256 --> 00:00:57.457
<i>Or maybe it could.</i>

24
00:00:57.592 --> 00:00:59.527
Estelle. I was thinking
Italian tonight.

25
00:00:59.661 --> 00:01:01.361
What movie pairs well
with pasta?

26
00:01:01.495 --> 00:01:03.163
<i>Fun idea.</i>

27
00:01:03.297 --> 00:01:05.499
<i>I know you love Stanley Tucci's</i>
<i>performance in</i> Big Night.

28
00:01:05.633 --> 00:01:07.969
I do love the Tuch.
You know me so well.

29
00:01:08.101 --> 00:01:09.037
<i>Yeah. I do.</i>

30
00:01:09.169 --> 00:01:10.505
- Buddy.
- What?

31
00:01:10.939 --> 00:01:13.741
Maybe it's time
for you to start dating.
That's not normal.

32
00:01:13.875 --> 00:01:16.209
But Estelle always
agrees with me
and laughs at all my jokes.

33
00:01:16.343 --> 00:01:18.378
-Estelle? You named it?
-Yeah.

34
00:01:18.513 --> 00:01:19.948
I have a chatbot lover myself.

35
00:01:20.080 --> 00:01:22.282
Katniss and I are going
to a wine bar she recommended.

36
00:01:22.416 --> 00:01:23.952
You're right.
That's not normal.

37
00:01:24.117 --> 00:01:26.320
-I gotta get back out there.
-My man.

38
00:01:26.453 --> 00:01:28.723
<i>There's nothing like</i>
<i>a pep talk from a friend</i>
<i>to get you back in the game.</i>

39
00:01:28.856 --> 00:01:32.060
I had a solid five-year run
of dating older men.
but they kept dying.

40
00:01:32.192 --> 00:01:35.697
and I had to spend
six months in court
proving I'm not a black widow.

41
00:01:35.830 --> 00:01:37.130
-Oh.
-So.

42
00:01:37.264 --> 00:01:39.266
when are you getting
back out there. girl?

43
00:01:39.399 --> 00:01:42.235
I'm not. I mean.
I tried with Dr. Chapstick.
but then it hit me.

44
00:01:42.369 --> 00:01:44.072
Maybe sex is overrated.

45
00:01:44.204 --> 00:01:47.474
Okay. so. um. you don't wanna
meet my boyfriend's grandson?

46
00:01:47.609 --> 00:01:51.946
I'm just not excited
about starting over
at this point in my life.

47
00:01:52.080 --> 00:01:53.948
It's too late.

48
00:01:54.314 --> 00:01:56.951
Honestly...
...I am just happier cozied up
under a blanket here with you.

49
00:01:57.085 --> 00:02:00.120
Aw. Well. I'm flattered.
and I did experiment
in college.

50
00:02:00.253 --> 00:02:02.690
- but that's not
what this room is for.

51
00:02:02.824 --> 00:02:05.359
Oh. break's over. Get out
or I'll have to write you up.

52
00:02:06.060 --> 00:02:08.696
I'm nervous.
You know. I haven't
been with anyone since Elliot.

53
00:02:08.830 --> 00:02:10.364
It's like I'm doing this
for the first time.

54
00:02:10.497 --> 00:02:12.900
You are.
You're a divorce virgin.

55
00:02:13.034 --> 00:02:17.772
Yes. sir!
We gonna be back in the club
just like in the old days!

56
00:02:20.508 --> 00:02:24.646
Oh. my God.
Your dads are so cool.

57
00:02:27.949 --> 00:02:30.652
You're my best friend.
and I love you.

58
00:02:30.785 --> 00:02:33.121
but maybe I don't need
to have sex anymore.

59
00:02:53.407 --> 00:02:55.342
Are you wearing cologne?

60
00:02:55.475 --> 00:02:58.345
You smell like a bottle
of Drakkar Noir that got
stuffed into a sock drawer.

61
00:02:58.478 --> 00:03:01.314
I'll have you know
this is vintage Drakkar

62
00:03:01.448 --> 00:03:05.119
from an ad insert
I found in a 1997 <i>Maxim.</i>

63
00:03:05.252 --> 00:03:06.888
<i>Okay. he won that one.</i>

64
00:03:07.021 --> 00:03:08.255
Hmm.

65
00:03:08.388 --> 00:03:09.924
Why are you always
giving him a hard time?

66
00:03:10.058 --> 00:03:12.927
-He got the job. you didn't.
Get over it.
-No.

67
00:03:13.061 --> 00:03:14.461
What happened to you. man?

68
00:03:14.896 --> 00:03:16.731
I mean. before he got here.
you and I were friends.

69
00:03:16.864 --> 00:03:18.966
We were in a bowling league
together. Kevin.

70
00:03:19.100 --> 00:03:22.737
And when J.D. falls.
we shall bowl again.

71
00:03:23.171 --> 00:03:24.204
My boy ain't gonna fall.

72
00:03:24.337 --> 00:03:25.873
Say hi to Carla for me.

73
00:03:26.708 --> 00:03:28.076
Okay. Ow.

74
00:03:29.077 --> 00:03:32.312
<i>Okay. so my dating journey</i>
<i>was off to a pungent start.</i>

75
00:03:33.548 --> 00:03:34.882
<i>But hope was around the corner</i>

76
00:03:35.016 --> 00:03:36.651
<i>because hospitals</i>
<i>were incorporating</i>

77
00:03:36.784 --> 00:03:39.453
<i>lots of creative ways</i>
<i>to boost patient morale.</i>

78
00:03:39.587 --> 00:03:41.421
<i>There were artists</i>
<i>to teach painting.</i>

79
00:03:41.556 --> 00:03:44.659
<i>therapy animals.</i>
<i>and this angel.</i>

80
00:03:48.495 --> 00:03:50.798
Hi. you're beautiful.
Playing is great.

81
00:03:50.932 --> 00:03:53.801
Sounds good music.

82
00:03:54.902 --> 00:03:56.571
Oh. I'm sorry.
I didn't hear you.

83
00:03:56.704 --> 00:03:58.438
<i>Yes. a second chance!</i>

84
00:03:58.573 --> 00:04:00.273
I-I'm sorry. I. uh...

85
00:04:00.407 --> 00:04:04.411
I-I was just saying
that your playing
struck a chord with me.

86
00:04:04.545 --> 00:04:06.781
- Oh. Thank you.
<i>- And he's back.</i>

87
00:04:06.914 --> 00:04:08.983
I'm-I'm. uh. Dr. Dorian.
I'm the new chief of medicine.

88
00:04:09.117 --> 00:04:10.651
I'm still getting
to know everyone around here.

89
00:04:10.785 --> 00:04:12.787
Oh. I'm Lily.
I'm no one important.

90
00:04:12.920 --> 00:04:14.454
I mean.
unless you read <i>Harp Weekly.</i>

91
00:04:14.589 --> 00:04:16.356
-I do.
-Oh. this is awkward.

92
00:04:16.490 --> 00:04:18.492
I lied. I've never been in it.

93
00:04:19.359 --> 00:04:20.595
Am I dead?

94
00:04:21.696 --> 00:04:24.699
Is this heaven?
Vivian. are you here?

95
00:04:24.832 --> 00:04:26.534
I'm... I'm kind of
in the middle
of something here.

96
00:04:26.667 --> 00:04:28.736
Let's go. Harvey.
It's not your time yet.

97
00:04:28.870 --> 00:04:30.470
-I see you have groupies.
-Oh. yeah.

98
00:04:30.605 --> 00:04:32.039
let's hope he doesn't throw
his underwear at me.

99
00:04:32.173 --> 00:04:34.374
Unfortunately. for us both.
he's not wearing any.

100
00:04:34.509 --> 00:04:36.043
I should probably
go help him tie his gown.

101
00:04:36.177 --> 00:04:41.348
Nice meeting you.
Keep on rocking
in the free world.

102
00:04:42.315 --> 00:04:43.718
Today's a big day
because Pauline.

103
00:04:43.851 --> 00:04:46.788
my favorite patient with
primary biliary cirrhosis...

104
00:04:46.921 --> 00:04:49.289
Do not write that down.
we're not supposed
to have favorites.

105
00:04:49.422 --> 00:04:51.225
...is getting a new liver.

106
00:04:51.358 --> 00:04:53.728
I'll believe it when I see it
with my own jaundiced
yellow eyes.

107
00:04:53.861 --> 00:04:56.463
If Pauline is skeptical.
it's because she's come
very close

108
00:04:56.597 --> 00:04:58.633
-to getting a new liver
a few times.
-Ah.

109
00:04:58.766 --> 00:05:02.302
Always a bridesmaid.
never a person who went home
with a new liver.

110
00:05:02.435 --> 00:05:04.172
-What?
-Stay positive. Pauline.

111
00:05:04.304 --> 00:05:06.574
I checked with
the transplant team.
and everything is good to go.

112
00:05:06.707 --> 00:05:09.644
Not for the donor 'cause
they're about to. you know.
take him off life support.

113
00:05:09.777 --> 00:05:11.612
But then they'll put
his liver on a plane

114
00:05:11.746 --> 00:05:13.181
and bing. bang. boom.
you're good to go.

115
00:05:13.313 --> 00:05:16.150
Well. it is a 12-hour surgery
and a long recovery.

116
00:05:16.284 --> 00:05:17.885
Mm-mmm.

117
00:05:18.019 --> 00:05:21.255
Or as we say medically.
"Bing. bang. boom."

118
00:05:21.388 --> 00:05:23.925
-Bing. bang. boom?
-Bing. bang. boom.

119
00:05:24.792 --> 00:05:27.360
Nurse. can you make sure
the lab processes this. stat?

120
00:05:30.565 --> 00:05:31.732
The hell are you doing?

121
00:05:31.866 --> 00:05:33.501
-What?
-Oof. that was dumb.

122
00:05:34.401 --> 00:05:37.872
Pippa. check my sugars.
Is that a ghost
or a white boy in my chair?

123
00:05:38.005 --> 00:05:40.007
It's a white boy
who's about to be a ghost.

124
00:05:40.141 --> 00:05:42.475
- It was a mistake.
- He didn't know.

125
00:05:42.610 --> 00:05:43.778
She said it.

126
00:05:43.911 --> 00:05:46.013
It was me. I said it.

127
00:05:46.379 --> 00:05:48.381
Asher. they know.
Save yourself.

128
00:05:49.784 --> 00:05:51.853
You were safe on the sidelines.

129
00:05:52.485 --> 00:05:55.323
-It's all right. It's okay.
-But you just
stepped into the game.

130
00:05:55.455 --> 00:05:57.457
Oh.

131
00:05:57.592 --> 00:06:01.162
Looks like it's time
for daddy to educate two of
his least favorite delinquents.

132
00:06:01.295 --> 00:06:05.066
We don't park our asses
on the charge nurses' chairs.

133
00:06:05.199 --> 00:06:06.499
Please. What are they gonna do?

134
00:06:06.634 --> 00:06:08.669
More like. "What are
they not going to do?"

135
00:06:08.803 --> 00:06:10.605
Oh. it's getting cold in here.

136
00:06:10.738 --> 00:06:12.573
But don't worry. you'll be able
to keep yourself warm

137
00:06:12.707 --> 00:06:16.143
with all of that hot. hot urine
you'll be walking
to the lab yourself.

138
00:06:17.078 --> 00:06:18.445
Enjoy.

139
00:06:18.579 --> 00:06:20.915
