00:19:32.006 --> 00:19:36.410
Hey. Just tell her.
She'd be crazy to say no.

450
00:19:38.613 --> 00:19:40.414
I've got to get back to work.

451
00:19:43.818 --> 00:19:45.119
Adopt a dog.

452
00:19:45.687 --> 00:19:47.387
-Sorry?
-That's the first thing I'd do

453
00:19:47.522 --> 00:19:49.857
when I get out of here.
You asked.

454
00:19:51.458 --> 00:19:53.795
Yeah.

455
00:19:57.197 --> 00:19:58.298
Thank you.

456
00:20:00.601 --> 00:20:03.638
<i>Only the heart knows</i>
<i>when it's ready</i>
<i>to let someone in again.</i>

457
00:20:05.272 --> 00:20:06.874
Thanks for getting it
here safely.

458
00:20:07.008 --> 00:20:10.277
No problem. Is there any place
to grab a coffee around here?

459
00:20:10.410 --> 00:20:12.714
Yeah. I can show you.

460
00:20:16.617 --> 00:20:20.588
<i>But sometimes</i>
<i>the heart just needs</i>
<i>a little more time to heal.</i>

461
00:20:29.063 --> 00:20:30.732
See. I don't need
to be out there dating.

462
00:20:30.865 --> 00:20:32.499
All I need is
two cozy weighted blankets.

463
00:20:32.633 --> 00:20:34.367
a good movie.
and my best friend.

464
00:20:34.502 --> 00:20:36.303
<i>I have to buy a white dress.</i>

465
00:20:36.804 --> 00:20:39.372
- J.D.. this movie's
really good.

466
00:20:39.507 --> 00:20:41.976
Don't tell Carla.
She's been begging me
to watch this for years.

467
00:20:42.110 --> 00:20:43.211
Look at Diane Lane.

468
00:20:43.343 --> 00:20:45.378
-She fine.
-Absolutely glowing.

469
00:20:45.513 --> 00:20:47.148
I wonder
what her skin-care routine is.

470
00:20:47.280 --> 00:20:49.282
'cause I've been so dry
in my T-zone.

471
00:20:49.650 --> 00:20:53.521
This is when you say.
"Oh. come on. J.D..
your T-zone is fire."

472
00:20:55.957 --> 00:20:58.358
Yeah. we're both
a bit tuckered out.

473
00:20:58.492 --> 00:21:00.561
-No.
-Yeah. that felt like too much.
